                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h5 class="card-title" style="font-size:xx-large;">Undergraduate Research Scholar Grants Awards</h5>
                        <p class="card-text">The primary purpose of Undergraduate Research Scholar (USR) is to enrich the research, scholarship and creative arts experience of the undergraduate student by involving the student in research collaboration with a faculty mentor. </p>
                        <p class="card-text">Students are encouraged to present a poster, or an equivalent demonstration of the research, on the Undergraduate Research Day.</p>
                        <p class="card-text">The student may request up to $300 (dry lab/creative activity) or $500 (wet lab) for supplies and expenses required for conducting the research or creative activity. </p>
                        <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary">View Student Award Recipients</a>
                        <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary">Apply for Student Research Scholar Grants Award</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
